{"word":"δυσμή","slug":"δυσμή","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>δυσμή</b></el> <el>(δυσμή, ἡ,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><el>δύω</el>\n<br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>= <a href='S:δύσις'><el>δύσις</el></a>, mostly in <a href='S:plural'>pl.</a>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>;\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><el>ἐπὶ δυσμῇσιν</el> at the point of <i>setting</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>the quarter of sunset, the west</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}